title: TV highlights: Ethan and Kate struggle to keep the town safe in the ‘Wayward Pines’ season finale
text:
Ethan (Matt Dillon) and Kate (Carla Gugino) in the “Wayward Pines” season finale. (Liane Hentscher/Fox) By — Lauren McEwen July 22 at 3:02 PM (All times Eastern.)
A former NFL cheerleader faces off against professional chefs on “Food Fighters” (NBC at 8).
Cat and Vincent are being targeted by an assassin on “Beauty and the Beast” (CW at 8). In an effort to lure the assassin away from their family and friends, Cat and Vincent pretend to elope.
FINALE WATCH: When the power is cut off in “Wayward Pines” (Fox at 9), Ethan and Kate work to keep the town safe and Nurse Pam tries to make Pilcher reconsider his decision.
One of the nude survivalists is forced to leave the Colombian badlands on “Naked and Afraid: Uncensored” (Discovery at 9).
On “Dates” (CW at 9), a man named David decides to give online dating another try but is upset when he realizes his date lied to him about her age.
A woman takes to sleeping on her patio when a floor-to-ceiling hoard takes over every room in her house on “Hoarders: Family Secrets” (Lifetime at 9).
“Man Vs Child: Chef Showdown” (FYI at 9) pits professional chefs against young cooking prodigies.
Johnny’s songwriting skills are put to the test when Gigi and her band challenge him to work while sober on “Sex&Drugs&Rock&Roll” (FX at 10).
On “Maron” (IFC at 10), a furious Marc steps in when his younger brother, Josh, is bullied while working at a corporate retreat.
On “Teen Mom 2” (MTV at 10), Adam and Chelsea prepare for their custody fight, Leah and Jeremy’s marriage is in trouble, and Jenelle’s fights with Nathan threaten her chances of getting custody of Jace.
Lina’s 40th birthday party is ruined by the hosts on “Married” (FX at 10:30).
A young man explains how abusing Adderall while studying at Columbia University threatened to ruin his future on “One Bad Choice” (MTV at 11).
The “Geeks Who Drink” (Syfy at 11) teams are headed by iJustine and Alan Tudyk.
“The Daily Show With Jon Stewart” (Comedy Central at 11) welcomes “Between the World and Me” author Ta-Nehisi Coates.
“True Detective” star Colin Farrell visits “Jimmy Kimmel Live” (ABC at 11:30) with musical guest Meghan Trainor.
Katie Holmes, Michael Showalter and David Wain stop by “The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon” (NBC at 11:30). Rapper Sage the Gemini and singer Nick Jonas perform.
— Lauren McEwen
